If a man had all that sort of knowledge that ever was, he would not be at all
the wiser; he would only be able to play with men, tripping them up and
oversetting them with distinctions of words. He would be like a person who
pulls away a stool from some one when he is about to sit down, and then laughs
and makes merry at the sight of his friend overturned and laid on his back.
